ques.p: To ask the Secretary of State for Transport what use (a) his Department and (b) service providers under contract to his Department make of (i) 0844 and 0845 telephone numbers and (ii) revenue-sharing telephone numbers for calls from members of the public; for which services such numbers are used; what prefixes are used for revenue-sharing numbers; how much revenue has accrued from revenue-sharing numbers in each of the last five years; what consideration his Department has given to introducing 03-prefixed telephone numbers for calls to all such services; and if he will make a statement.

reply.p: The Department for Transport and its Executive agencies operate three 0845 numbers and one 0844 number. The Driver and Vehicle Licensing Agency uses 0870 revenue-sharing numbers to provide access to nine public services. Information about these is set out as follows:

tr.td: Freight Best Practice helpline providing free information to promote operational efficiency
Motorway and trunk road information line
Garages hotline for checking MOT standards
Waste Electrical and Electronic Equipment helpline
Allows the public to ask general driving licence inquiries
Allows the public to ask general vehicle inquiries
Allows the public to ask advice about health conditions and their effect on driver licensing
Allows vocational drivers to seek advice regarding driver licensing
Allows the licensing of vehicles over the telephone
Allows customers to access information on DVLA's local office network
Helpline for customers using our online driving licence service
Allows customers to seek advice on the use of Smart Tachographs

reply.p: Revenue information from the DVLA services is only available since January 2005. The figures are shown by calendar year.

In addition, the Driving Standards Agency and the Vehicle and Operator Services Agency have recently switched from 0870 to 0300 numbers for calls made to their contact centres. Revenue information about these is set out as follows:

tr.td:
(1) DSA switched to 0300 line on 31 October 2008.
(2) VOSA switched to 0300 line on 30 September 2008.

reply.p: Consideration is currently being given to switching to 0300 numbers for the Freight Best Practice helpline and for the Highways Agency Information Line. DVLA had intended moving to 0300 numbers in line with Ofcom recommendations prior to the retraction of the Ofcom paper on use of 0870 numbers. Preparations to move to 0300 are still in place, once the Ofcom paper and recommendations are republished.

ques.p: To ask the Secretary of State for Children, Schools and Families how much his Department spent on (a) primary and (b) secondary school buildings in (i) Hemel Hempstead, (ii) Hertfordshire and (iii) England in 2007-08.

reply.p: A tentative estimate of the number of jobs that will be created from the acceleration of schools capital funding during the financial year 1 April 2009 to 31 March 2010 is 10,000.
